<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB7EF74FF42FD97FDECFC39" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FD97FE99FD3D" blockId="31.[151,1436,474,897]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FD97FEE7FD84" bold="true" box="[199,338,546,572]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Comments:</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded only in northern regions of South America. The record of this species for the ParNa Iguaçu expands its distribution in at least 3,000 Km. The individuals were collected only in light traps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FD3BFB74FD49" blockId="31.[151,1436,474,897]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FD3BFEEEFD10" bold="true" box="[199,347,654,680]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFFB7EF74FEEDFD3AFE58FD11" box="[360,493,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[158,1433,185,1743]" captionTargetId="figure-29@30.[151,1436,181,1744]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 14. Calling songs of species of Microcentrum (Phaneropterinae: Microcentrini) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A and B: a syllable of the calling song of M. lanceolatum, sonogram and spectrogram, respectively; C and D: a syllable of the calling song of M. marginatum, sonogram and spectrogram, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550087" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550087/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Fig. 14C, D</figureCitation>
): Males stridulate only during the night, producing hemisyllables that are not grouped, so echemes are not present. Each hemisyllable is formed by several pulses in crescendo that after reaching the peak start diminishing their intensity reaching a frequency that are smaller than the initial frequency.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FD4EFDE6FCAD" blockId="31.[151,1436,474,897]" box="[199,595,763,789]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FD4EFE1EFCAD" box="[199,427,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 11 ± 1.7 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FCAAFE45FC81" blockId="31.[151,1436,474,897]" box="[199,496,799,825]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FCAAFEF5FC81" box="[199,320,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 4.4 ± 2.8 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FCF6FCB6FCE5" blockId="31.[151,1436,474,897]" box="[199,771,834,861]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FCF6FE9BFCE4" box="[199,302,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Duration</emphasis>
: Pulse: 0.7 ± 0.3 ms; Syllable: 25 ± 1 ms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB7EF74FF42FCD2FDECFC39" blockId="31.[151,1436,474,897]" box="[199,601,871,897]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB7EF74FF42FCD2FEEAFC39" box="[199,351,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Pulse: 0.7 ± 0.06 ms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
